One type of harassment prohibited by this policy is sexual harassment. Sexual
harassment generally consists of:
• Unwelcome sexual advances;
• Unwelcome request for sexual favors; or
• Other unwelcome conduct of a sexual nature,
When: (1) submission to or rejection of such conduct is the basis for employment

under existing labor laws; or (3) such conduct has the purpose or effect of creating a
sexually offensive, hostile, or intimidating work environment that interferes with an
individual’s ability to perform the job.
Examples of sexual harassment include, but are not limited to:
• Requests or demands of sexual favors in exchange for favorable or preferential
treatment;
• Sexual jokes

Harassment
Workplace harassment prohibited under this policy is not limited to sexual harassment.
Statements or actions that offend or demean an individual and create an intimidating,
hostile, or offensive work environment based on a Protected Attribute are also
inappropriate and prohibited under this policy.
Reasonable management actions such as disciplinary actions are not harassment.
